{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give new fathers a right to six weeks paid paternity leave",
        "additional_details": "Dads should have 6 weeks off work with full pay so they\u2019ve got time to bond with their baby and help the mum, especially in cases where she has a cesarian section.\r\n\r\nIn the first 2 weeks, it can mainly be visits with the midwife for baby checks and mum checks, and visits from family. Dads need time to bond too.",
        "background": "Dads are only entitled 2 weeks paternity leave, at reduced pay. Dads are just as important as mums when it comes to bonding with a baby. 2 weeks leave is not enough and reduced pay is terrible for supporting a new family.",
